he bodies of two children have been found in the street in Orange Farm. At around 02:30 on Saturday, a 24-year-old woman reported her 6-year-old son and an 8-year-old girl, who is a family friend, missing to Orange Farm SAPS, police spokesperson Brigadier Mathapelo Peters said. "Police launched an immediate search for the two children who, according to the complainant, were last seen on Friday evening [at] around 19:00 when they were allegedly walking home from a hair salon," said Peters. At around 05:00 on Saturday, police received a call about the body of a child found on the street. Shortly after that, a passer-by discovered the second body, about 100 metres from the first one. "The children were certified dead by paramedics," said Peters.    